#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:2 7c74d451e2b54cc98c708a84f80ec5e7
msgid "Poisson Equation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:4 d3a867ae523a48a5b1ecaf419ae39b84
msgid ""
"Three scripts in ``examples/poisson/`` walk the Poisson problem through "
"TensorMesh's main features: a basic 2D solve, the same solver in 3D, and "
"h-adaptive refinement on an L-shaped domain whose re-entrant corner "
"produces a gradient singularity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:9 afdd64264389404b80922d33388c20a1
msgid ""
"For batched right-hand sides over many source terms (the ML data- "
"generation pattern), see :doc:`dataset` — that script lives under "
"``examples/dataset/poisson/`` so all batched-RHS workflows sit in one "
"place."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:14 5deec0fd9d864b41913516f1b537cc98
msgid "The strong form is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:16 1f72ab207cfc4780a5dd7889a30c0d81
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"-\\Delta u = f \\quad \\text{in } \\Omega,\n"
"\\qquad u = 0 \\text{ on } \\partial\\Omega,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:21 b1447d8607f340019c4f571d0c661906
msgid "with corresponding weak form"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:23 357652457b8142379fc3a43cdbf79341
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\int_\\Omega \\nabla u \\cdot \\nabla v \\,\\mathrm{d}\\Omega\n"
"\\;=\\;\n"
"\\int_\\Omega f\\, v \\,\\mathrm{d}\\Omega\n"
"\\quad \\forall v \\in H^1_0(\\Omega)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:30 59f0a686bb9b43fca5ab45d284420191
msgid ""
"Every example below realizes this with "
":class:`~tensormesh.LaplaceElementAssembler` for the stiffness, a "
":class:`~tensormesh.NodeAssembler` for the load, and "
":class:`~tensormesh.Condenser` for the homogeneous Dirichlet BC. The "
"ground-truth source field comes from "
":class:`~tensormesh.dataset.PoissonMultiFrequency`, which generates a "
"random truncated Fourier series whose analytical solution is also "
"available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:40 175f9735643146b59458f62be4fdff41
msgid "Basic 2D Poisson — ``poisson.py``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:42 e752b51008a84fe59836eeefd8790548
msgid ""
"The shortest end-to-end driver in the repo. The full pipeline fits in 25 "
"lines:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:45 1acff6a4b6a34121921f96824e2cdff2
msgid "examples/poisson/poisson.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:77 a02f1febd33440aa90cd07f83aef06aa
msgid "A few details worth pointing out:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:79 2dacf4285997453abc95cbb5b9ee2aea
msgid ""
"``assembler(mesh.points)`` returns a "
":class:`~tensormesh.sparse.SparseMatrix` built from the gradient bilinear"
" form. Pure-Python weak form, no custom kernels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:82 0963527e91ff43709b7a86942611a3b7
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"``FAssembler`` carries the source ``f`` through the integrand by name "
"(``point_data={\"f\": f}`` becomes the ``f`` kwarg in ``forward(v, f)``)."
" See :doc:`../user_guide/forms` for the full argument-dispatch contract."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:86 47080b2e40fd4d978f244f6923922ddc
msgid ""
"The :class:`~tensormesh.Condenser` shorthand ``K_, b_ = condenser(K, b)``"
" applies the Dirichlet boundary mask and folds prescribed values into the"
" RHS. ``recover(...)`` glues the boundary values back on after the solve."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:91 5c292f64a39f4beba284dec912be3846
msgid "2D Poisson — source term, FEM solution, and analytical solution"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:95 e314c22b8e714ac0bc271137aa32540f
msgid ""
"Output of ``poisson.py``: source ``f`` (left), FEM solution ``u_fem`` "
"(middle), and analytical reference ``u_analytical`` (right) on the unit "
"square. The two solution panels are visually indistinguishable at this "
"resolution — exactly what you want from a converged mesh."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:103
#: 92aa9c80e6b14a90a2dee809c3eaf0e7
msgid "3D extension — ``poisson_3d.py``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:105
#: fc9ea9f85a764f9aac9148b9048ae427
msgid "Identical machinery, swapping in a tetrahedral cube:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:112
#: 7734baa0b8554f95b0bd891b43728646
msgid ""
"The same :class:`~tensormesh.LaplaceElementAssembler` works because "
"``∇u·∇v`` is dimension-generic — the integrand has no hard-coded spatial "
"dimension. The output is written as ``poisson_3d.vtu`` for opening in "
"ParaView; the script also produces a half-domain cutaway PNG for quick "
"inspection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:118
#: ab1b8df4d79a4ae2b1f10b5542ad1497
msgid "3D Poisson on the unit cube, half-domain cutaway"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:123
#: b8e315a253634a79b6c7381aa3de8fbe
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Output of ``poisson_3d.py``: half-domain cut at :math:`x=0.5` showing the"
" FEM solution on the unit cube. The reported mass-weighted relative "
":math:`L^2` error against the analytical Fourier solution is "
":math:`\\mathrm{rel\\_L2} = 1.059\\times10^{-2}` at "
"``chara_length=0.05``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:131
#: 2665044818b44c6996131d17485bbc40
msgid "h-adaptive refinement on the L-shape — ``poisson_h_adaptivity.py``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:133
#: 24353f4c44b24a6eb0f73b0dd9e215d5
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"This is the one example on this page that goes well beyond the weak form."
" The L-shaped domain has a re-entrant corner at :math:`(0.5, 0.5)`, where"
" the exact solution :math:`u = r^{2/3}\\sin(2\\theta/3)` has a gradient "
"singularity. Uniform h-refinement converges only at rate "
":math:`\\mathcal{O}(N^{-1/3})` because the global error is dominated by "
"the corner; an adaptive scheme that shrinks elements near the singularity"
" recovers the optimal :math:`\\mathcal{O}(N^{-1})` rate in 2D."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:143
#: d1bc2d8c18694073b56af7e1dc699726
msgid ""
"The script implements the classical *solve → estimate → mark → remesh* "
"loop:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:146
#: 4d66ff9ed35649b28e2d54907c1eaed7
msgid "examples/poisson/poisson_h_adaptivity.py (essence)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:160
#: 6910e668af7042548af46943d4e22918
msgid "Three pieces are worth a closer look:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:162
#: a8173889650d4f65a59dfb93acd85c63
msgid ""
"**Non-homogeneous Dirichlet BC.** The exact solution is non-zero on the "
"boundary, so the script builds a :class:`~tensormesh.Condenser` with "
"``dirichlet_value=g`` evaluated from the singular formula at every "
"boundary node. Static condensation folds the boundary values into the "
"RHS; see :doc:`../user_guide/boundary_conditions`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:169
#: 9a607097a4914e90832790ea274a3f9e
msgid ""
"**Mass-weighted error.** :class:`~tensormesh.MassElementAssembler` "
"provides the :math:`L^2` norm operator: ``e^T M e``. The relative error "
"divides by :math:`\\sqrt{u_\\text{exact}^T M u_\\text{exact}}` for scale "
"invariance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:175
#: b8dfd2bcecce48989bbdf725fc18da42
msgid ""
"**Dörfler marking.** Mark every element whose error indicator exceeds "
":math:`\\theta\\, \\max(\\eta)` (default :math:`\\theta=0.5`) and halve "
"its size; coarsen the (almost-)error-free elements. The new size field is"
" fed to ``gmsh.model.mesh.setSizeCallback``, and the L-shape geometry is "
"re-meshed via OpenCASCADE booleans."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:181
#: 5846ad571cfd4b109c19609fed488781
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The output figure has three panels: convergence (adaptive vs uniform on a"
" log-log plot, with the :math:`\\mathcal{O}(N^{-1})` reference line), the"
" final adaptive mesh with elements clustered at the corner, and the FEM "
"solution itself."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:188
#: 49d2bf6e165143fca646dbf20fdb3a2f
msgid ""
"The remesh step calls into ``gmsh`` directly via the Python API and "
"requires ``gmsh >= 4.8`` for ``setSizeCallback``. Install with ``pip "
"install gmsh``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:192
#: 4e0a614f963b4d1187fe476b9b5252c4
msgid "L-shape adaptive vs uniform convergence, final mesh, FEM solution"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/poisson.rst:196
#: 4035c7385fa74ac3b8eb016d53f3e98f
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Output of ``poisson_h_adaptivity.py``. Left: relative :math:`L^2` error "
"vs DOF count — the adaptive curve recovers the optimal "
":math:`\\mathcal{O}(N^{-1})` rate (dotted line) while uniform refinement "
"stalls at :math:`\\mathcal{O}(N^{-1/3})` thanks to the corner "
"singularity. Middle: the final adaptive mesh (757 DOFs) clusters elements"
" at the re-entrant corner. Right: the FEM solution itself."
msgstr ""

